Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of nine (9) years.  That is six (6) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, on each count, concurrent.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Sex offender treatment;
3) Comply with requirements of the Sex Offender Registry;
4) Provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
5) No contact with the victim, S.M.E., DOB: 03-27-1992 or her family;
6) No contact with anyone under the age of 18 unless approved by the agent;
7) Maintain fulltime employment or job search;
8) Pay court costs of $1,228.00;
9) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
10) maintain absolute sobriety;
11) pay restitution - TBD.  Since counseling is on-going, the amount of restitution has not been determined yet.  However, it will be capped at $10,000.00.  The $5,000.00 cash bail is to be applied towards restitution, but is ordered held until the stipulation and order is drafted by the parties and signed by the court.  
The Court further orders that court ordered financial obligations shall be paid at the rate of 25% of the prison wages and work release funds.  The balance remaining at release from prison to be paid a condition of extended supervision at a rate determined by the supervising agent. 
The defendant has credit for 73 days.  
Minutes.
